The paper deals with a proof system for quantified Boolean formulas (QBFs) and its implementation in a QBF solver. This falls under the area of automated reasoning and theorem proving, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as it covers automated reasoning and search-based techniques used in the paper. 

cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also a likely category as it covers the study of logic and its applications in computer science, including automated reasoning and theorem proving. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as it covers the design and analysis of algorithms, which is relevant to the performance improvement reported in the paper. 

cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as it covers the study of programming languages and their semantics, which is relevant to the formalization of the Q-resolution calculus. 

cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category as it covers the study of the complexity of computational problems, which is not the main focus of the paper.
